title: Woman Searching for Couple She Photographed Getting Engaged in Paris
text:
Woman Searching for Couple She Photographed Getting Engaged in Paris July 1, 2015 
A proposal in Paris has stumped the planet. (Photo: Jen Hurd Bohn) 
It was the perfect marriage proposal. A gorgeous sunny day atop the Eiffel Tower in Paris, the skyline spreading out beyond. Jen Hurd Bohn, a good samaritan vacationing from California, snapped a few photographs of the exciting moment. But before she could offer the couple the engagement pictures, they raced off. 
Bohn is now searching for the mystery duo, and the photos have taken then internet by storm. 
Related: A French Guy’s Practical Tips For A Quick Trip to Paris 
Another shot of the mystery couple. (Photo: Jen Hurd Bohn/Facebook) 
“Saw this guy propose to this girl on the Eiffel Tower Sunday,” Bohn wrote on her Facebook page, according to UPI . “I wanted to send them the pics but was stuck in line. Help me find them!” 
So far, no takers. But the search goes on. Do you recognize this couple?
